# Repository Structure

Organize code by **pipeline stage**, matching the actual codebase.

```
/src
  /data              # Dataset loaders (ASQALoader)
  /retrieval         # QAPipeline, DocumentIndexer (FAISS)
  /training          # Retriever and generator training
  /filtering         # Answer quality filtering (CORE THESIS FOCUS)
  /evaluation        # RAGAS evaluator, retriever evaluator
  /configs           # YAML configuration files
  /utils             # Model cache, shared helpers
/rag-interference    # Self-RAG-style generative verifier experiment (Flan-T5)
/data
  /asqa              # ASQA dataset files (train.csv, dev.csv, labeled_asqa.csv)
/models              # Saved model checkpoints (e.g., models/answer_filter/)
/results             # Experiment outputs (predictions CSV, metrics JSON)
/notebooks           # Exploration, training, and analysis notebooks
/tests               # Unit tests mirroring /src structure
```

## Pipeline Flow

```
retrieve → generate → filter (answer quality) → accept/reject
```

- Filtering operates AFTER generation. Retrieval is assumed correct;
  the filter verifies whether the generated answer is faithful to the
  retrieved context. Interface: `(context, answer)` (NLI-style:
  premise = context, hypothesis = answer).
- Each stage is independent, testable, and replaceable
- Filtering logic lives ONLY in `/src/filtering/`
- Reusable logic goes in `/src/`, never in notebooks
- Experimental code and visualizations go in `/notebooks/`
- Self-RAG generative verifier experiment lives in `/rag-interference/` and may
  import shared utilities from `/src/` (e.g. `data_split`, `_extract_top1_context`)
